quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
37,103,"When both surrendered (to Allah's command) and Abraham flung the son down on his forehead, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,104,"We cried out: {1} “O Abraham,",footnotes:1:One section of the grammarians says that here “and” has been use to mean “then”; thus
37,105,"you have indeed fulfilled your dream. {1} Thus do We reward the good-doers.” {2}",footnotes:1:That is
37,106,"This was indeed a plain trial. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,107,"And We ransomed him with a mighty sacrifice, {1}",footnotes:1:“A great sacrifice”: A ram
37,108,"and We preserved for him a good name among posterity."
37,109,"Peace be upon Abraham."
37,110,"Thus do We reward the good-doers."
37,111,"Surely he was one of Our believing servants."
37,112,"And We gave him the good news of Isaac, {1} a Prophet and among the righteous ones. {2}",footnotes:1:Here
37,113,"And We blessed him and Isaac. Among the offspring of the two some did good and some plainly wronged themselves."
37,114,"Verily We bestowed Our favours on Moses and Aaron"
37,115,"and We delivered both of them and their people from the great calamity. {1}",footnotes:1:“A great distress”: the distress in which they were involved at the hands of Pharaoh and his people.
37,116,"We succoured them, and they gained the upper hand (against their enemies)."
37,117,"We granted them a Clear Book,"
37,118,"and showed them the Straight Way,"
37,119,"and preserved for them a good name among posterity."
37,120,"Peace be upon Moses and Aaron."
37,121,"Thus do We reward the good-doers."
37,122,"Surely both of them were among Our believing servants."
37,123,"Surely, Elias too was among the Messengers. {1}",footnotes:1:The Prophet Elias (peace be upon him) was from among the Israelite Prophets. He has been mentioned only twice in the Quran
37,124,"(Call to mind) when he said to his people: “Will you not fear Allah?"
37,125,"Do you call upon Baal {1} and forsake the Best of the Creators?",footnotes:1:Lexically
37,126,"Allah is your Lord and the Lord of your ancestors of yore.”"
